e SoE, Disjunction, Natures Recovery and Circle of Seasons. Moonfire would be nice but that I know of, ONE has dropped on Veeshan server. <br>
<br>
PotG is nice in groups where you don't have a cleric but it's more of a nuisance than anything on raids. Last night, I had to cast it on 4 people out of 36. Nice way to blow 4,800 mana... (tx wizards!) At least I got to damage shield the MT since there were no mages to be found. Was actually kind of confused when the MT asked for thorns... I had to do a /who mag to see if this guy had smoked crack prior to the raid.<br>
<br>
I'm not one to bitch. I take what's given to me and make the best of it but I do agree that I'd like to end one fight with some mana and feel like people would've noticed had I not been there.<br>
<br>
On a side note, there's a lot of bitching being done. How come no one has mentioned anything about our AC debuffs. We can debuff ac like it's nobody's business... Sure it takes 5 spells but if there's plenty of clerics and you don't mind aggro whoring, you can actually make a huge difference in a big fight.<br>
<br>
Laneela Silence<br>
Heirophant of Ixtlan<br>
60th Season<br>
~Veeshan Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uevilnight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EvilNight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 3:02:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=524>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conversation: What about Us! (State of The Druid)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  1. The majority of the discussion included Warrior and Rogue input. This petition does not (the Monk petition discussion was actually started by a Rogue). <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> The discussion was started by Arafain, who wanted to know why Monks were being flamed into oblivion on the Safehouse. Without his incredibly well written inquiry, and phenomenal willingness to discuss the issues with us, there's no way in hell we would have had that petition. Still, I don't think I saw more than thirty members of other classes present during those talks. We certainly didn't invite the other class boards to participate until well after the petition was drafted. I suspect this is much like what happened here... How much input have you Druids had over the past few weeks of discussion from Clerics and Shaman? <br>
<br>
We didn't have the total support of any other community but our own, all the way through the petition process. We had ten flamers from the other classes to every one person from the other classes who did support us. <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  2. VI gave Monks a specific place ingame damage-wise. The Monks simply gave damage ratios showing the disparity. Proving (quite simply) what was wrong. VI has yet to define the role of Druids by using such a claim. VI simply named them the Priest class (which implies healing to me). <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Well, that's true. What I see here are Druids showing the same sort of disparity but in terms of healing ability, not damage output. Shaman and Druids apparently should be tied as second tier healers, behind clerics. All other healers should be behind them. It's very clear to me that Shaman make better healers than Druids, so I see no reason not to give them a boost in healing power. <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  3. Monks then came up with ideas that stepped on the toes of no one. Not only that, we got the ok from the Warriors and Rogues that visited and added to the discussion. The Druids here did no such thing. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Well, not quite. We had the approval of a few select Rogues and Warriors who were quite happy to help out. If you check the boards there are similar notes of approval from some high level Clerics and Shaman here in the Druid signature thread and discussion pages. The majority of the other classes dislike the idea, just like the majority of rogues and warriors disliked ours. There were some truly capital flames on our signature thread, I had the pleasure of reading and responding to all of them. <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  To the defense of the Druids here, they didn't get the input that the Monks got, and to hear it now is understandable upsetting. But, to compare the Monk petition to this is off-base. Heck... even the ideas that didn't make it directly to the Monk class, showed up in AA skills. Funny how VI works no? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> I really don't know what sort of input they got because frankly I had heard nothing about this until two days ago. Really, I wouldn't have expected to. Monks don't have much say in this sort of thing, we aren't casters or healers. This thing has to be worked out between Clerics, Shaman, and Druids. I do agree about the AA skills... we thought we wouldn't be getting any defense upgrades but they later showed up there. Who knows how they plan to address this Druid issue. I wouldn't expect to see the fruits of it until the caster balancing goes in, and we don't know what they plan to do in Planes of Power either. <p>Raviel Darkfyre<BR>
56th Master of the Celestial Fists<BR>
<b>Insidious Blood</b>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukinamaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kinamaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 3:12:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=525>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Druids Role?</span><hr size=1> Maybe the druids role shouldn't be as a healer.  I would rank a druids abilities as follows.<br>
<br>
1. Travel. there are the best class for traveling, with ports, sow, invis.<br>
2. Damage. They do comparable damage to the other caster classes.<br>
3. Mob movement.  They have the best root and snare spells.<br>
4. Healing<br>
<br>
It seems that healing is the 4th ability of a druid.  So why do people want druids to heal?  The problem probably lies in the fact that melees do so much more damage than casters that doing anything to keep melees alive for any amount of time longer is of more benefit that the damage a druid/caster could deal.<br>
<br>
Maybe all casting classes need to have their damage output upped for raid situations.  Maybe druids should be given some lure DD spells.  If the damage done by druids and other casters nuking make the mob die fast enough to not need so much healing then they would be asked to nuke.<br>
<br>
It just seems to me that druids are more of a damage dealing class.  Clerics are the healing priest, shaman the debuffing/buffing priest and druids are the damage dealing priest.<br>
<br>
Another thought I had was about some spell to help keep raid mobs positioned properly.  It seems that proper positioning of some mobs is critical to an encounter. Could some spell be devised to help with this, would it be useful? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utettsuo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tettsuo1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 3:22:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=526>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~harulestokes/_uimages/StupendousManCharacter.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids Role?</span><hr size=1> Rav,<br>
<br>
My point was, the success of the Monk petition was largely due to the input from the other pure melee classes.  Just getting it pass whatever the number of Rogues and Warriors that participated in the petition discussion meant alot.  If the Druids had that amount of support from the other priest classes, the success of the petition may have been greatly increased.<br>
<br>
Sometimes, the class involved is too close to the problems to see the benefits it has.<br>
<br>
