Druzzil Ro</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utettsuo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tettsuo1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/10/02 12:23:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukiatek2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiatek2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 3:35:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=527>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: travel</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;1. Travel. there are the best class for traveling, with ports, sow, invis<br>
<br>
Yes we have gates, sow and invis.  That doesnt make us the best at it though.  The majority of ppl i know would much rather have a TL (usually to bind) from a wizard, than a gate from a druid.  They already have sow (via innate run speed, tboots, jboots, or horse), wizards can provide invis, and TL to bind is usually to nexus, where they camp. /shrug  Personally getting gates to the moon is not in my primary focus, although it would be nice so that my friends would not have to wait.  However, not having them means I dont get requests for them too (bonus in my opinion =)) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukesselicewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kessel Icewind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/02 3:42:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=528>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conversation: What about Us! (State of The Druid)</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure everyone will agree that druids, and shamans for that matter need some kind of boost in healing for high end game, no matter how minimal. The hard part is making is so druids/shamans do not infringe anymore on clerics, whether it be in aa/exp groups or raids.<br>
<br>
Although there are more issues than just healing brought up by this petition, it helps serve the purpose of making verant look and see that there is a problem, and unfortunately its not just with druids, but with all casters, especially concerning 55+ high end game/raids. If all verant has to offer us is mage focus items as their 'caster balancing' then I see no reason for me to start playing my druid again. The one class I started with and endured since April 99'. I'd rather quit EQ than level another  so-called 'needed' class. I have just as much right to the end game as every other class, no matter what path I chose to get there.<br>
<br>
Druids can solo pretty dam well but we're not the only classes so using that against us is getting very old.<br>
I don't want an upgrade in that respect so finding out how to increase our raid abilities without increasing our solo/group abilities is rather difficult.<br>
<br>
I can do without a new dot, without changing my epic, without ports to luclin but considering i'm asked to heal when I raid then to function adequately I need a little boost in that department.<br>
<br>
I'd be happy if they just removed the 10% penalty for healing. Least that would benefit shamans as well as druids. Then maybe our AA ability Healing Adept would mean we have to work a little bit to further increase our healing ability, even if only up to 10% more. I also think Natures Touch needs minor tweaking, like suggested. Reduce casting time slightly and refresh, even if it stays the same hp/mana ratio as cholorblast.<br>
<br>
I'm not advocation everything in the druid petition but some issues really need to be looked at and worked out a little if im going to continue to play. <p>Venerable Kessel Icewind<br>
60 Heirophant<br>
