/pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=542>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A compromise</span><hr size=1> A few more thoughts...<br>
<br>
First I do want to say I have read many of these posts from non druids and find many them intelligent and well thought out (but of course there is also a lot of &quot;we hate druids&quot; crap that is not worth too much attention). <br>
<br>
One of the better ones responded to the original petition point by point.  I wanted to throw out that the whole section on needing to heal 3 to 5 k dmg on a single target as a secondary healer really is valid.  Even a well run guild and a well run raid you will find someone (maybe a rogue, whatever) picks up agro and can't seem to shake it, and if you are the druid watching over them it is hard as hell (and it happens regularly).<br>
<br>
Anyway, I did want to suggest something that I have not stumbled across in the posts I read that might be acceptible as a short term measure for all:<br>
<br>
1) Remove the 10% penalty on healing from all classes that have it but increase the cleric to a 10% bonus (or even 15%).  The point here is that we don't care that clerics are ahead...we want to heal better under the conditions we are expected to.<br>
<br>
2) Make Healing Adept worth the trouble of getting.  As a druid, it is a low priority for me to pursue a whopping 12aaxp points for the end result of healing 10% better (taht is an extra 98 hp on my best heal for an investment of a huge amount of AAXP).  I am sure having read all the ratios for the other classes taht most clerics and shamans feel the same way.  Make this skill worth pursuing, and you will get druids (by definition high level ones, or well at least 50plus), shamans, and clerics ALL pursuing it.  Say first level 5% bonus, second 15%, and last 35% (actually I would go so far as to say 50% for the top level).  For a druid, that would mean the benefit of NT would go from 900 ish to 1200 ish, but clerics would be that much FARTHER ahead on their heals.  Again, this petition has nothing to do with druids compared to clerics.  It is all about druids compared to mobs.<br>
<br>
3) Give druids a group heal but make it for less HP than originally requested (if the original request won't pass).  I would be happy to be able to do Chloroblast level heals to the whole group at once for say 650 mana (no I did not do all the math to compare ratios to other classes but you get the idea).  It is clearly not as valuable as those clerics get (not sure how that stacks to pally), but WOULD be a huge benefit as a secondary healer where (hopefully and most of the time) you are dealing with people getting mostly AoE dmg.<br>
<br>
4)  Yes give us a better dot.  I don't care if it is not quite as powerful as requested, but there is a vast disparity in the effectiveness of druid dots vs other dot classes, and if you are playing a secondary healer a dot is usually all you can spare the mana on (if you do any dmg at all).  Verant IS looking at making changes so the same dot from different sources will stack (ie two druids could both cast Winged Death on the same mob).  This will be a huge increase in the raid contribution from necros, and also from druids and shamans.<br>
<br>
5) Epic was the one thing I really did not care too deeply about in the original petition.  It is great for solo but little else, but so is the necro epic.  Bugs me that necro epic bumps ours instead of just not stacking (ie whoever gets there first will have it stick).  Still, my favorite solution would be the mob is &quot;IMMUNE to the snare portion of this effect&quot; message which would mean you could still at least use it in raid situations.<br>
<br>
Anyway, heart of it is maybe the solution on heals can be found in AAXP, and one group heal.<br>
<br>
I still fully endorse the original post, but know that asking is not getting.  We do need some heal fix, and we really do need a way to be more valuable on high end raids. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=221&stop=240>12</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=241&stop=260>13</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=261&stop=280>14</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=281&stop=3